{
  "local_port": 44042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I cook manchurian?",
  "response": "Manchurian is a popular Indo-Chinese dish that typically features vegetables or chicken coated in a spicy sauce. Here\u2019s a simple recipe for Vegetable Manchurian, which can easily be adapted if you prefer chicken by substituting vegetable ingredients with minced chicken.\n\n### Vegetable Manchurian Recipe\n\n#### Ingredients:\n\n**For the Vegetable Balls:**\n- 1 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, beans, cabbage, etc.), finely chopped\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour (maida)\n- 2-3 tablespoons cornflour\n- 1-2 green chilies, finely chopped (adjust to taste)\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 1 teaspoon soy sauce\n- Salt, to taste\n- Pepper, to taste\n- Oil, for frying\n\n**For the Manchurian Sauce:**\n- 2 tablespoons oil\n- 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste\n- 2-3 green chilies, slit (adjust to taste)\n- 1 medium onion, chopped\n- 1 bell pepper, chopped (optional)\n- 2-3 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon tomato ketchup\n- 1 tablespoon chili sauce (adjust to taste)\n- 1 teaspoon vinegar (optional)\n- 1-2 green onions, chopped for garnish\n- Salt, to taste\n- 1 teaspoon cornflour mixed in 2 tablespoons water (for thickening)\n\n#### Instructions:\n\n**1. Make the Vegetable Balls:**\n   - In a bowl, mix the finely chopped vegetables, all-purpose flour, cornflour, ginger-garlic paste, soy sauce, salt, and pepper. Adjust the consistency; it should be firm enough to shape into balls.\n   - Form small balls (about the size of a golf ball) from the mixture.\n   - Heat oil in a pan for frying. Once hot, deep-fry the balls until they are golden brown and crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n**2. Prepare the Manchurian Sauce:**\n   - In a separate pan or wok, heat 2 tablespoons of oil on medium heat.\n   - Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies, saut\u00e9 for a minute until fragrant.\n   - Add chopped onion and bell pepper, stir-fry until they become translucent.\n   - Stir in the soy sauce, tomato ketchup, chili sauce, vinegar (if using), and adjust salt to taste.\n   - Mix in the cornflour-water mixture to thicken the sauce. Cook for a couple of minutes until the sauce is glossy and thickened.\n\n**3. Combine:**\n   - Gently add the fried vegetable balls into the sauce, and toss them carefully to coat. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes so the flavors meld together.\n\n**4. Garnish and Serve:**\n   - Garnish with chopped green onions and serve hot with steamed rice or noodles.\n\nEnjoy your homemade Vegetable Manchurian! If you're making Chicken Manchurian, follow the same steps but use minced or finely chopped chicken instead of mixed vegetables for the balls and ensure it's cooked thoroughly.",
